# AI Starter Pack

When the user says "set up my coding environment", "bootstrap my agent", "install my starter pack", or wants their usual agent defaults configured:

Load and execute `skills/ai-starter-pack/SKILL.md` from this repo. It contains the full install menu (rails, caveman, design, command-hygiene, rtk), dedup logic, and write instructions per component.

For Cursor specifically, read `skills/ai-starter-pack/references/hosts.json` and use the `cursor` host entry. It is the source of truth for the Cursor context/rule surface and target format.

All paths in SKILL.md are relative to the `skills/ai-starter-pack/` directory.
